The '''Place of Bones''' was a location on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] after it was [[Terraforming/Legends|Vongformed]] into [[Coruscant/Legends#Yuuzhan'tar|Yuuzhan'tar]]. A swampy boneyard near the [[Great Western Sea/Legends|Western Sea]], it was where the Yuuzhan Vong's [[biot]]s went to die, and where young [[Warrior caste|Warriors]] were trained. When followers of the [[Jeedai heresy|''Jeedai'' heresy]] rescued three hundred prisoners at the [[Place of Sacrifice]], [[Shimrra Jamaane]], the [[Supreme Overlord]] of the Yuuzhan Vong, ordered three thousand [[Shamed Ones]] executed at the Place of Bones, whether they were heretics or not. After the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar]], the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] held Yuuzhan Vong prisoners at the Place of Bones.<ref name="TUF">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force]]''</ref>

